Wet conditions are likely to continue in several parts of the country throughout the week, the Kenya Meteorological Department has said. Meteorological Services Director Peter Ambenje said areas in the Central highlands, including Nairobi, the Coast and Southeast Lowlands will continue receiving light to moderate rainfall. Parts of the Northeast may experience enhanced rainfall at the beginning of the forecast period. The Northeast regions comprises of Marsabit, Mandera, Wajir, Garissa and Isiolo. Other regions in the country will be sunny, with a few areas experiencing evening showers. According to the latest seven-day forecast covering April 3-9, sunny intervals will be experienced in the morning and afternoon showers and thunderstorms in the Lake Victoria Basin, highlands west of the Rift Valley, Central and South Rift Valley.